commit message: front: Updated all translations, added Italian.
cleanup: Fix some errors in German translation

front: Commented out frame-advance and gameshark buttons in map screen.

Just uncomment them when the back-end is implemented.

front: Added input maps for specific gamepads, for internal dev.

At the moment these aren't accessible via the GUI. I added them so that
developers can hard-code the input map if necessary for debugging.

Cleanup: Various typos/code changes.

- Simplify clamping in PeripheralController.java
- Fix a typo
- Extended description, etc.

front: Hard-coded options to disable analog normalization & de-bias.

To facilitate debugging OUYA and wired PS3 controller.

bugfix: I think this fixes a cast exception seen in bugsense.

If a user had previously set a binary cheat, it was persisted as a
boolean in the datafile.  Now all cheats are persisted as integers,
even if they're binary.  A user with an out-of-date datafile would have
gotten a class cast exception when reading the boolean as an integer. I
*think* this fixes that problem.  Note that this only affects alpha
testers who have set binary cheats in previous release candidates.

bugfix: Player maps are persisted to default location again.

This means cheat options are also persisted to the default data file as
well, and can be reset from the settings menu like all the rest.
cleanup: Change variable name for clarity.

front: Added option to disable cheat menu altogether (speedup loading).

The transition when you change the checkbox state is a little funny,
but it works.
front: Removed animation when showing/hiding cheats category.
front: Added cheats icon to Play menu.

front: Removed unnatural transition animations between Menu and Play.

None of the other preference screens are animated when the user nav-
igates up and down the hierarchy. So we remove it here as well. (The
reason it's animated in the first place is because the Play menu
resides in its own activity.)

Update version string.
And fixed a small typo
